EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring notification to community boards and council members of applications for issuance of alteration permits for cellular telephone antennas and equipment.
EventItemMatterName: Notification to community boards and council members of applications for issuance of alteration permits for cellular telephone antennas and equipment.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to noise levels during protests and demonstrations.
EventItemMatterName: Noise levels during protests and demonstrations.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Civil Service and Labor
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the federal government to only purchase military uniforms made wholly in the United States, and to give New York City its fair share of military uniform purchasing contracts.
EventItemMatterName: Federal government to only purchase military uniforms made wholly in the US.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the appropriate committee of the Council of the City of New York to hold a hearing to review federal standards and guidelines for determining where to locate traffic control devices and whether they are appropriate for New York City.
EventItemMatterName: Review federal standards and guidelines for determining where  to locate traffic control devices and whether they are appropriate for NYC.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the prohibition of inhumane activities and practices used in rodeos.
EventItemMatterName: Prohibition of inhumane activities and practices used in rodeos.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring that commercial shopping establishments that maintain a parking area of at least 200 spaces install, maintain and operate surveillance cameras in order to deter crime.
EventItemMatterName: Require commercial shopping establishments that maintain a parking area of at least 200 spaces install, maintain and operate surveillance cameras in order to deter crime.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Consumer Affairs
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to prohibiting locksmiths and car dealers from reproducing ignition keys in specific circumstances.
EventItemMatterName: Prohibiting locksmiths and car dealers from reproducing ignition keys in specific circumstances.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Consumer Affairs
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to prohibiting the resale of undergarments.
EventItemMatterName: Prohibiting the resale of undergarments.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the collection of claims on behalf of the city of New York.
EventItemMatterName: Collection of claims on behalf of the city of New York.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to horse drawn cabs.
EventItemMatterName: Horse drawn cabs

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the enforcement of stop-work orders issued by the department of buildings.
EventItemMatterName: Enforcement of stop-work orders issued by the department of buildings.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to dividing the 109th precinct into two distinct subdivisions.
EventItemMatterName: Dividing the 109th precinct into two distinct subdivisions.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon Governor Pataki and the New York State Legislature to request that the United States Congress amend or repeal the Professional and Amateur Sports Protection Act to allow states to legalize betting on sporting events, and further calling upon the United States Congress to change this law so that New York State can legalize betting on sporting events and use all revenue generated from this activity for education funding.
EventItemMatterName: Amend or repeal the Professional and Amateur Sports Protection Act.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to remove New York City Transit and MTA Bus Company from the control of the Metropolitan Transportation Authority (MTA) and transfer control to the city of New York or in the alternative to cede greater decision making authority in the planning and operations of NYCT and MTA Bus Company to the City of New York.
EventItemMatterName: Remove NYC Transit and MTA Bus Company from the control of the Metropolitan Transportation Authority (MTA).

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Fire and Criminal Justice Services
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Mayor and the Fire Department of the City of New York to abide by the laws as set forth in the Laws of New York, 2002, Chapter 468, Part A, §3, concerning the full active employment status of James J. Corrigan, William Wren, and Phillip T. Hayes by the Fire Department of the City of New York on September 11, 2001, including their eligibility for all rights and privileges as active duty firefighters.
EventItemMatterName: Mayor and the FDNY to abide by the laws as set forth in the Laws of New York, 2002.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to amend Sections 458 and 458-a of the New York Real Property Tax Law, in relation to extending partial property tax exemption provisions of such sections to the school tax portion of New York State property taxes for qualified veterans.
EventItemMatterName: Extending partial property tax exemption provisions of such sections to the school tax portion of NYS property taxes for qualified veterans.

EventItemActionText: This SLR was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass bills introduced by Senator Dilan, S.1282, and Assembly Member Robinson, A.2455, “AN ACT to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the registration of property and designation of mailing address”.
EventItemMatterName: The registration of property and designation of mailing address (S.1282, A.2455).

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the State to simplify the enrollment and recertification process to end the practice of “churning” Medicaid managed care recipients, and thereby ensure access to consistent, long-term, preventive health care and achieve cost savings as intended by the system.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Mayor to declare an emergency health disaster in the Bronx and implement a plan of prevention and treatment as a result of the alarmingly high rates of HIV/AIDS, smoking, obesity, diabetes, mental disorders, teen pregnancy and child asthma in the Bronx.
EventItemMatterName: Mayor to declare an emergency health disaster in the Bronx.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health

EventItemMatterName: Address disparities in life expectancy between poor communities of color and wealthy communities in NYC.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Youth Services

EventItemMatterName: Summer Youth Employment Program

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Youth Services
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the appropriate committee of the Council of the City of New York to conduct hearings on the findings of the October 15, 2004 Report of the National Institutes of Health, concluding that counseling programs for families and youth-at-risk are more effective in deterring adolescent violence than “get tough” programs, group detention facilities, treating juveniles as adults in the criminal justice system and adult lecturing programs.
EventItemMatterName: Conduct hearings on the findings of the October 15, 2004 Report of the National Institutes of Health.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation

EventItemMatterName: Repeal the 1998 amendments to the Higher Education Act of 1965.
